{"expireTime":9007200804686336000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-html-9fe32b4474e320ebea8deab6d94c6298-gatsby-remark-graphvizgatsby-remark-code-titlesgatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-responsive-iframegatsby-remark-autolink-headersgatsby-remark-prismjsgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-smartypants-","val":"<p><a href=\"https://zeit.co/now\">ZEIT Now</a> is a <a href=\"https://zeit.co/docs/v2/getting-started/introduction-to-now/\">cloud platform for serverless deployment</a> that you can use to deploy your Gatsby projects and <a href=\"https://zeit.co/docs/v2/domains-and-aliases/aliasing-a-deployment/\">alias them</a> to your personal domain or a free <code class=\"language-text\">.now.sh</code> suffixed URL.</p>\n<p>This guide will show you how to get started in a few quick steps:</p>\n<h2 id=\"step-1-getting-started-with-gatsby\"><a href=\"#step-1-getting-started-with-gatsby\" aria-label=\"step 1 getting started with gatsby permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Step 1: Getting Started with Gatsby</h2>\n<p>If you haven’t already <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/quick-start\">set up a Gatsby project</a> you can do so by first installing Gatsby globally:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> --global gatsby-cli</code></pre></div>\n<p>Then generate a project with the following command:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">npx gatsby new <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>your project name<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"step-2-getting-now\"><a href=\"#step-2-getting-now\" aria-label=\"step 2 getting now permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Step 2: Getting Now</h2>\n<p>You can use Now by installing <a href=\"https://zeit.co/docs/v2/getting-started/installation/#now-desktop\">Now Desktop</a>, which also installs Now CLI and keeps it up-to-date automatically.</p>\n<p>To install Now CLI quickly with npm, use the following:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> -g now</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"step-3-preparing-to-deploy\"><a href=\"#step-3-preparing-to-deploy\" aria-label=\"step 3 preparing to deploy permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Step 3: Preparing to Deploy</h2>\n<p>With Now CLI installed, we can go on to deploy our previously setup Gatsby project by first creating a <code class=\"language-text\">now.json</code> file with the following contents:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-code-title\">now.json</div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"json\"><pre class=\"language-json\"><code class=\"language-json\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">\"version\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">\"name\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"my-gatsby-project\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">\"builds\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"src\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"package.json\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"use\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@now/static-build\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"config\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token property\">\"distDir\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"public\"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>This <code class=\"language-text\">now.json</code> file will allow us to do several things, specifically:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Use the <a href=\"https://zeit.co/blog/now-2\">latest Now 2.0 version</a> of <a href=\"https://zeit.co/docs/v2/platform/overview/\">the platform</a></li>\n<li>Set the project name to <code class=\"language-text\">my-gatsby-project</code></li>\n<li>Use the <a href=\"https://zeit.co/docs/v2/deployments/official-builders/static-build-now-static-build/\">@now/static-build builder</a> to take the <code class=\"language-text\">package.json</code> file as an entrypoint and use the <code class=\"language-text\">public</code> directory as our content directory</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The final step is to add a script to the <code class=\"language-text\">package.json</code> which will build our application:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-code-title\">package.json</div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"json\"><pre class=\"language-json\"><code class=\"language-json\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">\"scripts\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    ...\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"now-build\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"npm run build\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"step-4-deploying\"><a href=\"#step-4-deploying\" aria-label=\"step 4 deploying permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Step 4: Deploying</h2>\n<p>You can deploy your application by running the following in the root of the project directory, where the <code class=\"language-text\">now.json</code> is:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">now</code></pre></div>\n<p>That’s all! Your application will now deploy, and you will receive a link similar to the following: <a href=\"https://my-gatsby-project-fhcc9hnqc.now.sh/\">https://my-gatsby-project-fhcc9hnqc.now.sh/</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"references\"><a href=\"#references\" aria-label=\"references permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>References:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://zeit.co/examples/gatsby/\">Deploying Gatsby with Now</a></li>\n</ul>"}